**Regional Communications Manager**

**Based in New York City**

At the forefront of building the nation’s labor movement, 32BJ SEIU is changing the narrative around important social and economic issues facing working families. As the largest union in the country, 32BJ SEIU represents over 175,000 property service workers including cleaners, apartment building workers, security officers, airport workers, schools, and food service employees in 12 states and Washington, DC.

Our mission is to build and grow a diverse, effective, and politically independent organization of workers to change lives for the better, improve our communities, and build a more just society for present and future generations. Headquartered in New York City, our members have fought for and achieved high standards including paid sick days, expanded access to healthcare, and a higher minimum wage (Fight for $15). We continue to fight for higher wage and benefit standards for thousands of not yet organized service workers. We are committed to engaging and developing our diverse membership to lead in our organizing, political, social justice, and contract campaigns.

The Regional Communications Manager is a member of the Communications team, covering 32BJ’s New York and New Jersey Districts. The Manager supervises three staff and reports to the Communications Director.

**Responsibilities include:**

· Develop, drive and execute internal and external communications strategies, including defining strategic objectives, goals and metrics; lead multi-faceted communications plans, and ensure messaging consistency;

· Lead a team of communicators with expertise in public relations, digital communications and internal communications to effectively develop comprehensive communications plans;

· Use member communication tools, including email, text, design and distribution of collateral materials among others, to increase member engagement and participation in various union activities;

· Build relationships with reporters who cover labor, immigration, politics and social justice issues to yield earned media regarding the union’s work;

· Post content on the union’s social media channels for the assigned region;

· Engage vendors as needed for photography, videography, translation or design services;

· Manage a calendar of regional and union-wide priorities, ensuring communications deliverables are produced on time and are effective;

· Participate in cross-departmental campaign/district strategy and planning meetings, bringing communications expertise to the table;

· Work with other Regional Managers and the Director to help lead and foster collaboration across the Department.

**Qualifications:**

While no one candidate will possess every quality outlined for this position, the successful candidate will bring many of the following professional skills and personal attributes:

· A minimum of five years of experience in communications or campaign management in labor, advocacy or related work; must include supervisory experience;

· Ability to lead, manage effectively, take initiative, handle multiple priority projects and meet deadlines;

· Experience in strategic communications planning and capacity building in large, multi-faceted organizations;

· Demonstrated experience as an effective project manager in a fast-paced, campaign-oriented work environment;

· Adept at problem-solving and creative thinking in crisis situations;

· Ability to plan and execute communications for a variety of audiences, including union members, workers who are organizing to join the union, elected officials and other ally/stakeholder audiences, as well as media;

· Facility with digital tools and openness to expanding skills in this area;

· Media relationships, and background in working with reporters; experience developing creative press pitches;

· Strong writing skills, strong sense of effective story-telling and proven ability to write quickly, concisely and persuasively;

· Demonstrated commitment to social and economic justice, especially work with union members, low-wage and/or immigrant communities;

· Strong preference for candidates with written and verbal Spanish language fluency, including ability to perform accurate written translations.

**Work Environment**

· This is a full-time position based in New York City.

· This position requires travel to other locations and events, including worksites, rallies, member meetings, and some out-of-state gatherings.

**Physical Demands**

· This position occasionally requires long and irregular hours, including some nights, weekends and holidays.

· This position is largely computer/office based, with in-person and Zoom meetings. There will be some required off-site meetings, and regular campaign activities such as bargaining meetings, hearings, outdoor rallies and marches, and other events.

**COMPENSATION & BENEFITS**

The salary for this role is $95,000-$99,568. 32BJ offers a full benefits package that includes an employer-paid medical, dental and vision plan (for full-time employees and their qualified dependents) and retirement benefits, including a defined benefit pension plan and 401K.

**APPLICATION**

Please send a resume and letter of interest to HR@seiu32bj.org. Please use **“Comm Manager – NY/NJ”** in the subject line of your email. Please include where you saw the job.

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: $95,000.00 - $99,568.00 per year

Benefits:

* 401(k)
